article.headline: Rice 81, Boise State 61
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Michael Harris had 30 points and 15 rebounds to lead Rice to an 81-61 win over Boise State on Thursday night. Yamar Diene scored 20 points and eight rebounds for Rice (10-3, 2-0 Western Athletic). Boise State (9-3, 1-1) was led by Aaron Haynes with 20 points, including 16 in the first half. Jason Ellis had 16 points and 10 rebounds. Rice outscored Boise State 20-8 in the closing minutes of the first half to lead 44-33 at halftime. The Owls led by 19 midway through the second half but Boise State rallied to get within nine points. A 17-6 run by Rice late in the second half extended its lead. Rice shot 48 percent from the field to 37 percent by Boise State.
